headline: 2 Cash-Producing Stocks with Exciting Potential and 1 We Ignore
summary: While strong cash flow is a key indicator of stability, it doesn’t always translate to superior returns. Some cash-heavy businesses struggle with inefficient spending, slowing demand, or weak competitive positioning.

headline: Alzheimer's Disease: When All Else Fails
summary: Most candidates fail to show meaningful clinical benefit in Alzheimer's. Read why I am against investing in companies based solely on their Alzheimer's drug programs.
